                    </div>
                    <span>A Clockwork Orange is a gruesome story of a teen living in a futuristic world in which the streets are ruled by chaos and violence.  The protagonist(using this term loosely) is named Alex and is the leader of a street gang who spend their time fighting, stealing, and raping.  This goes on until Alex is caught and put in a program designed to reform him.  A Clockwork Orange is an interesting, but disturbing look into violent criminal actions and a desire that is can only be motivated by an obvious lack of a moral compas.  If the reader can get past the excrutiatingly frustrating use of random slang dialogue and the graphic depictions of rape and other violent crimes, then A Clockwork Orange is a very interesting read that reallly forces one to take a look a the violence in our own society.  A Clockwork Orange was not an easy read, but it was still a very interesting one.  Therefore, I would give it a 7 out of 10.</span>
                  
